g/wiki/Special:EntityPage/Q4973099#sitelinks-wikipedia \"Edit interlanguage links\")\n\n-   [Article](/wiki/Brodmann_area_9 \"View the content page [c]\")\n-   [Talk](/wiki/Talk:Brodmann_area_9 \"Discuss improvements to the content page [t]\")\n\n English\n\n-   [Read](/wiki/Brodmann_area_9)\n-   [Edit](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=edit \"Edit this page [e]\")\n-   [View history](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=history \"Past revisions of this page [h]\")\n\n Tools\n\nTools\n\nmove to sidebar hide\n\nActions\n\nGeneral\n\n-   [What links here](/wiki/Special:WhatLinksHere/Brodmann_area_9 \"List of all English Wikipedia pages containing links to this page [j]\")\n-   [Related changes](/wiki/Special:RecentChangesLinked/Brodmann_area_9 \"Recent changes in pages linked from this page [k]\")\n-   [Upload file](//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:File_Upload_Wizard \"Upload files [u]\")\n-   [Permanent link](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&oldid=1310819399 \"Permanent link to this revision of this page\")\n-   [Page information](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=info \"More information about this page\")\n-   [Cite this page](/w/index.php?title=Special:CiteThisPage&page=Brodmann_area_9&id=1310819399&wpFormIdentifier=titleform \"Information on how to cite this page\")\n-   [Get shortened URL](/w/index.php?title=Special:UrlShortener&url=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FBrodmann_area_9)\n\nPrint/export\n\n-   [Download as PDF](/w/index.php?title=Special:DownloadAsPdf&page=Brodmann_area_9&action=show-download-screen \"Download this page as a PDF file\")\n-   [Printable version](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&printable=yes \"Printable version of this page [p]\")\n\nIn other projects\n\n-   [Wikimedia Commons](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Brodmann_area_9)\n-   [Wikidata item](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Special:EntityPage/Q4973099 \"Structured data on this page hosted by Wikidata [g]\")\n\nAppearance\n\nmove to sidebar hide\n\nFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\n\nPart of the frontal cortex in the brain of humans and other primates\n\nBrodmann area 9\n\n[![](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Brodmann_area_9.png/250px-Brodmann_area_9.png)](/wiki/File:Brodmann_area_9.png)\n\n[![](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Brodmann_Cytoarchitectonics_9.png/250px-Brodmann_Cytoarchitectonics_9.png)](/wiki/File:Brodmann_Cytoarchitectonics_9.png)\n\nDetails\n\nIdentifiers\n\n[Latin](/wiki/Latin \"Latin\")\n\n*area frontalis granularis*\n\n[NeuroNames](/wiki/NeuroNames \"NeuroNames\")\n\n[1024](http://braininfo.rprc.washington.edu/centraldirectory.aspx?ID=1024)\n\n[NeuroLex](/wiki/NeuroLex \"NeuroLex\") ID\n\n[birnlex\\_1740](http://uri.neuinfo.org/nif/nifstd/birnlex_1740)\n\n[FMA](/wiki/Foundational_Model_of_Anatomy \"Foundational Model of Anatomy\")\n\n[68606](https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/FMA/?p=classes&conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fpurl.org%2Fsig%2Font%2Ffma%2Ffma68606)\n\n[Anatomical terms of neuroanatomy](/wiki/Anatomical_terms_of_neuroanatomy \"Anatomical terms of neuroanatomy\")\n\n\\[[edit on Wikidata](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q4973099 \"d:Q4973099\")\\]\n\n**Brodmann area 9**, or **BA9**, refers to a [cytoarchitecturally](/wiki/Cytoarchitecture \"Cytoarchitecture\") defined portion of the [frontal](/wiki/Frontal_lobe \"Frontal lobe\") [cortex](/wiki/Cerebral_cortex \"Cerebral cortex\") in the brain of humans and other [primates](/wiki/Primate \"Primate\"). Its cytoarchitecture is referred to as [granular](/wiki/Anatomy_of_the_cerebellum#Granular_layer \"Anatomy of the cerebellum\") due to the concentration of [granule cells](/wiki/Granule_cell \"Granule cell\") in layer IV.[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1) It contributes to the [dorsolateral](/wiki/Dorsolateral_prefrontal_cortex \"Dorsolateral prefrontal cortex\") and [medial](/wiki/Medial_frontal_gyrus \"Medial frontal gyrus\") [prefrontal cortex](/wiki/Prefrontal_cortex \"Prefrontal cortex\").\n\n## Functions\n\n\\[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=edit&section=1 \"Edit section: Functions\")\\]\n\nResearch has identified the area as being variously involved in short term memory, verbal fluency, error detection, auditory verbal attention, and inductive reasoning;[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-pmid15833592-2)[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-pmid12953304-3)[\\[4\\]](#cite_note-pmid17274022-4)[\\[5\\]](#cite_note-pmid16340161-5)[\\[6\\]](#cite_note-pmid9175134-6) functions also include evaluating recency, overriding automatic responses, inferring the intention of others, inferring deduction from spatial imagery, and attributing intention.[\\[7\\]](#cite_note-pmid8981471-7)[\\[8\\]](#cite_note-pmid16859418-8)[\\[9\\]](#cite_note-pmid8541472-9)[\\[10\\]](#cite_note-pmid11958963-10)[\\[11\\]](#cite_note-pmid10094258-11) In one investigation, the area saw engagement while study participants counted a series of auditory stimuli.[\\[12\\]](#cite_note-pmid18489960-12) The area displays lower levels of energy consumption in individuals suffering from bipolar disorder.[\\[13\\]](#cite_note-pmid21176034-13)\n\nThe area found on the left hemisphere is at least partially responsible for working memory, empathy, idiom comprehension, and self-criticism.[\\[14\\]](#cite_note-pmid22956832-14)[\\[15\\]](#cite_note-pmid11496124-15)[\\[16\\]](#cite_note-pmid9287369-16)[\\[17\\]](#cite_note-pmid17490991-17)[\\[18\\]](#cite_note-pmid19770047-18) Additional capabilities encompass processing pleasant and unpleasant emotional scenes,[\\[19\\]](#cite_note-pmid9352521-19) and attending to negative emotions.[\\[20\\]](#cite_note-pmid21733287-20)\n\nOn the right hemisphere, the region is involved in the attribution of intention, theory of mind, working memory, and [spatial memory](/wiki/Spatial_memory \"Spatial memory\").[\\[21\\]](#cite_note-pmid10679187-21)[\\[22\\]](#cite_note-pmid12169265-22)[\\[23\\]](#cite_note-pmid14642465-23)[\\[24\\]](#cite_note-pmid11960021-24)[\\[25\\]](#cite_note-pmid11798278-25)[\\[26\\]](#cite_note-pmid16516248-26)[\\[27\\]](#cite_note-pmid12126506-27) Recognition and recall are also capabilities,[\\[28\\]](#cite_note-pmid12457762-28)[\\[29\\]](#cite_note-pmid9010011-29)[\\[30\\]](#cite_note-pmid10088902-30)[\\[31\\]](#cite_note-pmid8134341-31)[\\[32\\]](#cite_note-pmid11346889-32) while further functions in this area encompass planning, calculation, religiosity, semantic and perceptual processing of odors, recognition of others' emotions, and attention to positive emotions.[\\[33\\]](#cite_note-pmid11880658-33)[\\[34\\]](#cite_note-pmid12914254-34)[\\[35\\]](#cite_note-pmid10678698-35)[\\[36\\]](#cite_note-pmid11328359-36)[\\[37\\]](#cite_note-pmid9950717-37)[\\[38\\]](#cite_note-pmid16317710-38)[\\[20\\]](#cite_note-pmid21733287-20)\n\n## Guenon\n\n\\[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=edit&section=2 \"Edit section: Guenon\")\\]\n\n**Brodmann area 9** also exists in the frontal lobe of the [guenon](/wiki/Guenon \"Guenon\"). Brodmann-1909 regarded it on the whole as topographically and cytoarchitecturally [homologous](/wiki/Homology_\\(biology\\) \"Homology (biology)\") to the [granular frontal area 9](/wiki/Granular_frontal_area_9 \"Granular frontal area 9\") and [frontopolar area 10](/wiki/Frontopolar_area_10 \"Frontopolar area 10\") in the human. Distinctive features (Brodmann-1905): Unlike [Brodmann area 6](/wiki/Brodmann_area_6 \"Brodmann area 6\") (Brodmann-1909), area 9 has a distinct internal granular layer (IV); unlike [Brodmann area 6](/wiki/Brodmann_area_6 \"Brodmann area 6\") or [Brodmann area 8](/wiki/Brodmann_area_8 \"Brodmann area 8\") (Brodmann-1909), its internal pyramidal layer (V) is divisible into two sublayers, an outer layer 5a of densely distributed medium-size [ganglion cells](/wiki/Ganglion \"Ganglion\") that partially merges with layer IV, and an inner, clearer, cell-poor layer 5b; the [pyramidal cells](/wiki/Pyramidal_cell \"Pyramidal cell\") of sublayer 3b of the external [pyramidal layer](/wiki/Pyramidal_layer \"Pyramidal layer\") (III) are smaller and sparser in distribution; the external [granular layer](/wiki/Granular_layer_\\(cerebral_cortex\\) \"Granular layer (cerebral cortex)\") (II) is narrow, with small numbers of sparsely distributed [granule cells](/wiki/Granule_cell \"Granule cell\").[\\[39\\]](#cite_note-39)\n\n## Image\n\n\\[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=edit&section=3 \"Edit section: Image\")\\]\n\n-   [![Animation.](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Brodmann_area_9_animation_small.gif/120px-Brodmann_area_9_animation_small.gif)](/wiki/File:Brodmann_area_9_animation_small.gif \"Animation.\")\n    \n    Animation.\n    \n-   [![front view.](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Brodmann_area_9_frontal.jpg/120px-Brodmann_area_9_frontal.jpg)](/wiki/File:Brodmann_area_9_frontal.jpg \"front view.\")\n    \n    front view.\n    \n-   [![Lateral view.](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Brodmann_area_9_lateral.jpg/120px-Brodmann_area_9_lateral.jpg)](/wiki/File:Brodmann_area_9_lateral.jpg \"Lateral view.\")\n    \n    Lateral view.\n    \n-   [![Medial view.](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/Brodmann_area_9_medial.jpg/120px-Brodmann_area_9_medial.jpg)](/wiki/File:Brodmann_area_9_medial.jpg \"Medial view.\")\n    \n    Medial view.\n    \n\n## See also\n\n\\[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=edit&section=4 \"Edit section: See also\")\\]\n\n-   [Brodmann area](/wiki/Brodmann_area \"Brodmann area\")\n-   [Dorsomedial prefrontal cortex](/wiki/Dorsomedial_prefrontal_cortex \"Dorsomedial prefrontal cortex\")\n-   [List of regions in the human brain](/wiki/List_of_regions_in_the_human_brain \"List of regions in the human brain\")\n\n## References\n\n\\[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Brodmann_area_9&action=edit&section=5 \"Edit section: References\")\\]\n\n1.  **[^](#cite_ref-1)** Vasković, Jana (2023-11-03), [*Cytoarchitecture of cerebral cortex*]